WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.750 --> 00:00:02.119
The Employee Service Center

1
00:00:02.319 --> 00:00:05.539
is NCDIT's internal self-service portal

2
00:00:05.760 --> 00:00:08.899
where employees and internal users can request services,

3
00:00:09.319 --> 00:00:10.239
report issues,

4
00:00:10.470 --> 00:00:11.640
and find information.

5
00:00:13.220 --> 00:00:16.879
It is intended for NCDIT employees and internal users

6
00:00:17.100 --> 00:00:19.680
and is separate from the government services portal

7
00:00:19.860 --> 00:00:21.399
used for external users

8
00:00:21.500 --> 00:00:22.819
and service engagement.

9
00:00:24.920 --> 00:00:28.680
The Employee Service Center organizes services into major categories,

10
00:00:29.069 --> 00:00:30.520
including human resources,

11
00:00:30.680 --> 00:00:31.319
IT,

12
00:00:31.600 --> 00:00:32.700
and risk and compliance.

13
00:00:33.930 --> 00:00:37.860
Within IT, topics are grouped around Services and Service Offerings,

14
00:00:38.099 --> 00:00:39.979
making it easier to browse services,

15
00:00:40.259 --> 00:00:40.810
requests,

16
00:00:40.819 --> 00:00:42.020
and support resources.

17
00:00:42.950 --> 00:00:44.150
Selecting a topic

18
00:00:44.270 --> 00:00:45.770
opens a content page

19
00:00:46.029 --> 00:00:49.779
where related requests and resources are gathered together in one place.

20
00:00:50.069 --> 00:00:54.450
This taxonomy helps keep services easier to navigate as content continues to grow.

21
00:00:54.790 --> 00:00:56.060
From these topic pages,

22
00:00:56.270 --> 00:00:58.150
related requests are grouped together so you

23
00:00:58.150 --> 00:00:59.909
can quickly choose the service you need.

24
00:01:01.330 --> 00:01:04.120
Related services are grouped into shared request forms,

25
00:01:04.319 --> 00:01:06.830
reducing the need for multiple separate forms.

26
00:01:07.129 --> 00:01:09.709
Dynamic forms adjust based on your selections,

27
00:01:09.930 --> 00:01:12.069
so only relevant information is collected.

28
00:01:17.410 --> 00:01:18.589
If something is not working,

29
00:01:18.889 --> 00:01:20.940
the Current Status panel provides a quick

30
00:01:20.940 --> 00:01:23.589
view of known service issues and degradations.

31
00:01:24.550 --> 00:01:26.199
If you need help with a technical issue,

32
00:01:26.279 --> 00:01:28.379
select "Experiencing an issue?"

33
00:01:28.959 --> 00:01:30.319
to open the incident form.

34
00:01:31.500 --> 00:01:34.190
The incident form also includes current system status,

35
00:01:34.349 --> 00:01:37.849
helping you check whether an issue is already known before submitting a report.

36
00:01:40.199 --> 00:01:42.709
You can also open the full System Status page

37
00:01:42.889 --> 00:01:43.889
to review outages,

38
00:01:43.970 --> 00:01:44.769
degradations,

39
00:01:45.050 --> 00:01:46.849
and plan maintenance in more detail.

40
00:01:48.650 --> 00:01:51.519
You can also use search in the growing knowledge base

41
00:01:51.699 --> 00:01:56.010
to find guidance and answers without submitting a request or incident.

42
00:01:56.290 --> 00:01:58.889
Search returns requests and knowledge articles together,

43
00:01:59.019 --> 00:02:01.519
helping you quickly find the most relevant result.

44
00:02:03.220 --> 00:02:06.220
Knowledge articles provide step-by-step guidance and

45
00:02:06.220 --> 00:02:09.059
supporting information for common tasks and questions.

46
00:02:09.339 --> 00:02:11.720
Knowledge content will continue to grow over time,

47
00:02:12.059 --> 00:02:14.179
supporting more self-service across the portal.

48
00:02:15.929 --> 00:02:18.860
The homepage also provides a view of your active items,

49
00:02:19.179 --> 00:02:19.979
including requests,

50
00:02:20.089 --> 00:02:20.580
incidents,

51
00:02:20.660 --> 00:02:21.250
tasks,

52
00:02:21.259 --> 00:02:22.130
and surveys.

53
00:02:22.380 --> 00:02:23.419
You can check progress,

54
00:02:23.660 --> 00:02:24.449
review status,

55
00:02:24.580 --> 00:02:26.500
and open records directly from here.

56
00:02:28.380 --> 00:02:30.779
My Tickets remains available from the top navigation

57
00:02:30.779 --> 00:02:32.830
menu wherever you are in the portal,

58
00:02:33.139 --> 00:02:34.690
alongside My Tasks,

59
00:02:34.699 --> 00:02:37.880
where you'll find any approvals or other to do's assigned to you.

60
00:02:38.669 --> 00:02:40.740
For users who also work in fulfillment roles,

61
00:02:40.869 --> 00:02:44.539
Fulfiller View provides direct access to your fulfillment workspace.

62
00:02:44.830 --> 00:02:47.929
This allows you to move quickly between the Employee Service Center

63
00:02:47.929 --> 00:02:50.460
and the tools you use to manage and complete work.

64
00:02:50.669 --> 00:02:52.729
And from your fulfillment workspace,

65
00:02:52.919 --> 00:02:56.050
you can return to the employee service center at any time

66
00:02:56.270 --> 00:02:59.490
by opening the All menu and searching for Employee Center.

67
00:03:01.759 --> 00:03:03.619
Whether you're requesting a service,

68
00:03:04.039 --> 00:03:05.039
reporting an issue,

69
00:03:05.320 --> 00:03:06.500
finding information,

70
00:03:06.759 --> 00:03:08.029
or tracking your work,

71
00:03:08.320 --> 00:03:09.800
the Employee Service Center

72
00:03:09.919 --> 00:03:11.979
is your starting point for internal support

73
00:03:12.240 --> 00:03:13.820
across NCDIT.
